{
    "id": "renderutil",
    "lang": "en-US",
    "name": "RenderUtil",
    "description": "Change how an object looks: recolor it, swap its texture or material, tile and offset the texture, and show or hide it.",
    "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/renderutil",
    "tags": [
        "uniscript",
        "renderutil",
        "color",
        "texture",
        "material",
        "appearance"
    ],
    "previous": {
        "name": "UIUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/uiutil"
    },
    "next": {
        "name": "ColorUtil",
        "link": "/docs/uniscript/en-US/colorutil"
    },
    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "RenderUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`RenderUtil` changes how an object **looks** — its color, its texture (the image wrapped around it), and whether it's visible at all. Use it to flash an enemy red when hit, recolor a team's gear, or hide an object's graphics."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Coloring an object"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`SetColor` tints an object. You can give it four numbers (red, green, blue, and opacity, each `0`–`1`) or a ready-made color value from [ColorUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/colorutil)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Flash the object bright red (with four numbers).",
                "RenderUtil.SetColor(this, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0);",
                "",
                "// Or use a named color.",
                "RenderUtil.SetColor(this, ColorUtil.Red());"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-006",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Textures and materials"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-007",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "A **texture** is the image painted onto an object's surface; a **material** combines a texture with a shader (the rule for how light hits it). These let you swap them while the game runs."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-008",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`SetTexture(this, texture)`", "Swaps the image on the object's surface."],
                ["`SetShader(this, shader)`", "Changes the shader (a number choosing a built-in look)."],
                ["`SetMaterial(this, shader, texture)`", "Sets the shader and texture together."],
                ["`SetTextureTiling(this, tiling)`", "Repeats the texture across the surface (the `x` and `y` of the vector set how many times)."],
                ["`SetTextureOffset(this, offset)`", "Shifts the texture — animate this for scrolling effects like water or a conveyor belt."],
                ["`SetTextureSettings(texture, filterMode, wrapModeU, wrapModeV)`", "Fine-tunes a texture: `filterMode` (`0` crisp/pixelated, `1` smooth) and wrap modes (`0` repeat, `1` clamp)."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-009",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Scroll a texture to fake flowing water.",
                "void OnUpdate()",
                "{",
                "    float t = Time.GameTime() * 0.2;",
                "    RenderUtil.SetTextureOffset(this, VectorUtil.New(t, 0.0, 0.0));",
                "}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-010",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Showing and hiding the graphics"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-011",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`SetVisibility` hides or shows just an object's **graphics** while leaving the object itself active (it can still move and collide). The `includeSubItems` value extends this to child objects too."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-012",
            "tag": "code",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "lines": [
                "// Make the object invisible, including its children.",
                "RenderUtil.SetVisibility(this, false, true);"
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-013",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`SetVisibility` only hides the look — the object still exists and reacts. To turn an object off entirely, use `SetUniObjectActivation` from [UniObjectUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/uniobjectutil#block-018)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-014",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-015",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Returns",
                "Method",
                "Parameters"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`void`", "`SetColor`", "`uniscript, float r, float g, float b, float a`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetColor`", "`uniscript, color color`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetMaterial`", "`uniscript, int shader, object texture`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetShader`", "`uniscript, int shader`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetTexture`", "`uniscript, object texture`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetTextureSettings`", "`object texture, int filterMode, int wrapModeU, int wrapModeV`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetTextureTiling`", "`uniscript, vector3 tiling`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetTextureOffset`", "`uniscript, vector3 offset`"],
                ["`void`", "`SetVisibility`", "`uniscript, bool visible, bool includeSubItems`"]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-016",
            "tag": "tip",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "For building and reading the color values used by `SetColor`, see [ColorUtil](/docs/uniscript/en-US/colorutil)."
        }
    ]
}
